Ing '''Shas''' ({{lang-he|ש״ס}}, metung a acronym para king ''Shomrei Sfarad'', lit. ''Bante nang Sfarad's (ning Torah)'') metung yang [[ultra-orthodox]] a partidu pulitikal a relihyosu king [[Israel]].<ref name="EB">{{cite web | url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/755711/Shas | title=Shas | publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica Online | work=Encyclopædia Britannica 2011| accessdate=21 December 2011}}</ref> Mitátag ya kanitang 1984 king lalam ning pamanibala nang [[Rabbi]] [[Ovadia Yosef]], a sadyang [[Pekapun a rabbi|Sephardic a pekapun a rabbi]] (''Sephardi chief rabbi''),  a menatiling ispiritual nang pekapun angga king kayang kamatayan anyang Octubre 2013. Keraklan, magsilbi yang pekakatawan no reng relihyosung Hudyung [[Sephardic Haredim|Sephardic]] ampong [[Mizrahi]].<ref name="EJ">{{cite web | url=http://go.galegroup.com/ps/i.do?id=GALE%7CCX2587518235&v=2.1&u=unizur&it=r&p=GVRL&sw=w | title=Shas | publisher=Michael Berenbaum and Fred Skolnik (Ed.), Encyclopaedia Judaica, 2nd ed. Vol. 18. Detroit: Macmillan Reference USA | work=Encyclopaedia Judaica | year=2007 | accessdate=21 December 2011 | pages=419–420}}</ref>

Anyang mumuna, malati yang grupung pulitikal a makabasi king lahi o kabilyan a etniku, ing Shas, a king salukuyan yang kapat a pekamaragul a partidu king [[Knesset]] o Parlamentu ning Israel, at, agpang king ''[[The Jewish Daily Forward]]'', "the unchallenged kingmaker of Israeli politics".<ref name="Forward">{{cite web | url=http://forward.com/articles/147999/ | title=Shas Sets Up Shop in U.S. | work=The Jewish Daily Forward | date=20 December 2011 | accessdate=21 December 2011 | author=Guttman, Nathan}}</ref> Manibat kanitang 1984, pane yang kayabe king manibalang koalisyon, ing [[Labor Party (Israel)|Labor]] man o ing [[Likud]] ing makalukluk a partidu.<ref name="EB"/><ref name="cnn"/> King salukuyun, 2013, atilu king oposisyun deng kayanib ning Shas, kayabe ya ing Labor<ref name="cnn">{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/03/14/world/meast/israel-new-government |publisher=CNN |date=March 14, 2013 |title=Israel's new government excludes ultra-religious |first=Ben |last=Brumfield |first2=Mike |last2=Schwartz}}</ref> uling king e pamikasundu kareng aliwang partidung maka-wanan king  koalisyon nang Netanyahu tungkul king pamag-serbisyu da reng ultra-Orthodox king militar.<ref name="mekelberg">{{Cite news |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/views/2013/03/18/Israel-Coalition-of-the-will-ing-to-be-in-power.html |first=Yossi |last=Mekelberg |date=18 March 2013 |title=Coalition of the will(ing) to be in power |publisher=Al-Arabiya}}</ref>

